title: Football: Vianney's Brown earns offensive game ball of Week 6
text:
MORE HOLMDEL – The final statistical line recorded by St. John Vianney’s Anthony Brown in the Lancers' Week 6 victory over Raritan isn’t typical for an NFL game, let alone a high school tilt.
In fact, one could describe the Boston College commits efforts as extraordinary…unless of course you’re speaking to St. John Vianney’s first year coach Derek Sinisky.
“Anthony had a great game, but it’s kind of like the same old thing for us,” Sinisky said of Brown’s big game, after his Lancers delivered a 56-26 triumph over the Rockets. “For a lot of people who haven’t seen him play, they’ll probably see this as a great, great game by him. But to us its sort of commonplace because we’re so used to it.”
